"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-newsletters-archive-2024-07-books-briefing-best-books-olympics-679250\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Literature and sports are a team that can go for gold.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 54, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Literature\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 10}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 21}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 32}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 53}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an edition of the Books Briefing, our editors' weekly guide to the best in books.Sign up for it here.\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 165, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an edition\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 74}, {\"ngram\": \"the Books Briefing\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 96}, {\"ngram\": \"our editors' weekly guide\", \"from\": 98, \"to\": 123}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This week, I have been engaging in a high-stakes round of planning.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a high-stakes round\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"planning\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flurry of text messages lighting up my phone will dictate how my next two weeks will go, and my window for solidifying the logistics is closing swiftly.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The flurry\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 245}, {\"ngram\": \"text messages\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"my phone\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 283}, {\"ngram\": \"my next two weeks\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"my window\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"the logistics\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am talking, of course, about the plans my friends and I are making for watching the Olympics at local bars: what events we will prioritize, which patios have the best TVs, and who's free during key moments in Paris.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999295142, \"rank\": 7.060958583270079e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the plans\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"my friends\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"local bars\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"what events\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 513}, {\"ngram\": \"patios\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"the best TVs\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"key moments\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(I am partial, as I told one pal, to \\\"gymnastics, swimming, women's soccer, and horses.\\\")\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one pal\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics, swimming, women's soccer\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But first, here are three new stories fromThe Atlantic's books section: The Olympics can stir up sports fandom in the least jock-inclined out there by playing on a heady mix of patriotism, awe, drama, and spectacle.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 917, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three new stories\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"Atlantic's books section\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"sports fandom\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"a heady mix\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"patriotism\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"awe\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"drama\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacle\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Amanda Parrish Morgan wrote this week, \\\"Athleticism, exercise, and sports all lend themselves to heightened narrative stakes.\\\"\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 921, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanda_Tanen\", \"score\": 0.9240878222643879, \"rank\": 0.08176738745314405, \"text\": \"Amanda\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanda_Tanen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amanda_Tanen\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5020197989458507e-15, \"text\": \"Parrish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\", \"score\": 0.7057959246591475, \"rank\": 0.4158281598031419, \"text\": \"Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athleticism\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"exercise\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"heightened narrative stakes\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully for the bookworms among us, she adds, \\\"writers know this well.\\\"\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bookworms\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"writers\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her list ofbooks that will inspire you to moveis useful all year, however.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her list ofbooks\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Hutchinson'sEndureexplores the evergreen question of how to determine-and reach-our physical limits; Julie Otsuka's novelThe Swimmersis a philosophical meditation on how water frees and transforms a group of people who are certainly not top competitors.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1198, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Hutchinson\", \"score\": 0.9999998635244176, \"rank\": 1.364740078776405e-07, \"text\": \"Alex Hutchinson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Hutchinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Hutchinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Otsuka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julie Otsuka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Otsuka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Otsuka\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evergreen question\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"our physical limits\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"a philosophical meditation\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"how water frees\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1384}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"top competitors\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, Carey Baraka also wrote about a different set ofbooks sports fans should read: Romesh Gunesekera's novelThe Matchliterally narrates a high-stakes game-in this case, a pivotal cricket bout-and Nick Hornby'sFever Pitchis a chronicle of the thrill and heartbreak of being a fan.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.556856394503783e-25, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barakah\", \"score\": 0.9999999999804459, \"rank\": 1.963197462014016e-11, \"text\": \"Baraka\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barakah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barakah\"}, {\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romesh_Gunesekera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Romesh Gunesekera\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romesh_Gunesekera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romesh_Gunesekera\"}, {\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Hornby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3750973269978745e-47, \"text\": \"Nick Hornby\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Hornby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Hornby\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a different set ofbooks sports fans\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"a high-stakes game\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1616}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"a pivotal cricket bout\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"Pitchis\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"a chronicle\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"the thrill\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"a fan\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there are also books that make great companions to the Games themselves.Sophia Stewart recently wroteabout Vicki Valosik's new history of artistic swimming,Swimming Pretty; this summer, the U.S. artistic-swimming team will compete in the Olympics for the first time in 16 years.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potter_Stewart\", \"score\": 0.6275350161812675, \"rank\": 0.3487379878156968, \"text\": \"Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potter_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potter_Stewart\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"great companions\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"Vicki Valosik's new history\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic swimming\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1902}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. artistic-swimming team\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1993}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"16 years\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rita Bullwinkel's novel,Headshot, follows a group of underdog women boxers-and the story \\\"makes us into fans\\\" of the scrappy competitors,Rowan Hisayo Buchanan writes.\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rita_Bennett\", \"score\": 0.9999991752869154, \"rank\": 6.986070518057618e-07, \"text\": \"Rita\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rita_Bennett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rita_Bennett\"}, {\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_video_game_terms\", \"score\": 0.9999998897969878, \"rank\": 1.0906203994934102e-07, \"text\": \"Headshot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_video_game_terms\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_video_game_terms\"}, {\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Hisayo_Buchanan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rowan Hisayo Buchanan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Hisayo_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rowan_Hisayo_Buchanan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"underdog women boxers\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"the scrappy competitors\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Readers can always pick up obvious choices too-something likeThe Boys in the Boat, about the gold-medal-winning U.S. men's rowing team at the 1936 Berlin Games.\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999920032678, \"rank\": 5.658963917102694e-09, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Readers\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"obvious choices\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2235}, {\"ngram\": \"too-something likeThe Boys\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2262}, {\"ngram\": \"the Boat\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1936 Berlin Games\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And today,Michael Waters has collected a list of books that will deepen our understanding of the Games themselves.\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Michael Waters\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"a list\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"books\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2408}, {\"ngram\": \"our understanding\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think I will have some Olympic nonfiction in my bag as I cheer for the United States and Norway (a major perk of being from a dual-nationality family), but balancing heavy history with pure fun is important too.\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998906764691, \"rank\": 1.0696475715437276e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2560, \"end\": 2566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9994149904475654, \"rank\": 0.00029637040863210115, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some Olympic nonfiction\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"my bag\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2522}, {\"ngram\": \"a major perk\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2580}, {\"ngram\": \"a dual-nationality family\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2620}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy history\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"pure fun\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A friend of mine is reading Meryl Wilsner's frothy soccer romance novelCleat Cute, and I may have to borrow it when she's done.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2810, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A friend\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"mine\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"Meryl Wilsner's frothy soccer romance\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"novelCleat Cute\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eight Books That Will Inspire You to Move Your Body By Amanda Parrish Morgan Athleticism, exercise, and sports all lend themselves to heightened narrative stakes, and writers know this well.\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2875, \"end\": 2882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5020197989458507e-15, \"text\": \"Parrish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maxfield_Parrish\"}, {\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\", \"score\": 0.7057959246591475, \"rank\": 0.4158281598031419, \"text\": \"Morgan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_le_Fay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Eight Books\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2823}, {\"ngram\": \"Your Body\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2863}, {\"ngram\": \"exercise\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"heightened narrative stakes\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 2973}, {\"ngram\": \"writers\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read the full article.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the full article\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So Many Olympic Exertions, by Anelise Chen Athena is in her eighth year of an American Studies Ph.D. program, struggling to complete her dissertation.\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3109, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_studies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.419332982113573e-33, \"text\": \"American Studies\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_studies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_studies\"}, {\"begin\": 3126, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doctor_of_Philosophy\", \"score\": 0.9999998527337193, \"rank\": 1.4723657153648535e-07, \"text\": \"Ph.D.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doctor_of_Philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doctor_of_Philosophy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many Olympic Exertions\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3055}, {\"ngram\": \"Anelise Chen Athena\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3079}, {\"ngram\": \"her eighth year\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3101}, {\"ngram\": \"her dissertation\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After she hears that her ex-boyfriend has died by suicide, just getting through the day becomes an act of endurance.\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her ex\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"suicide\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3239}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3269}, {\"ngram\": \"an act\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3284}, {\"ngram\": \"endurance\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3297}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which is fitting, because Athena's dissertation is about sports, and suddenly she can not stop watching videos of marathon runners crossing finish lines in great agony.\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3325, \"end\": 3331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athena\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.326672378417606e-13, \"text\": \"Athena\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athena\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3356, \"to\": 3362}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"marathon runners\", \"from\": 3413, \"to\": 3429}, {\"ngram\": \"finish lines\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3451}, {\"ngram\": \"great agony\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Written in propulsive segments that move seamlessly between fiction and nonfiction, the novel reads in part like a fascinating hybrid essay on the psychological impact of competition and the ubiquity of sports metaphors, which Chen points up to illustrate how much the mentality of never quitting, of winning at all costs, has seeped into our society's obsession with achievement.\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3695, \"end\": 3699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\", \"score\": 0.8365024348998971, \"rank\": 0.14264776926386544, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"propulsive segments\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3498}, {\"ngram\": \"fiction\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3535}, {\"ngram\": \"nonfiction\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"the novel\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"a fascinating hybrid essay\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3607}, {\"ngram\": \"the psychological impact\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3635}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3650}, {\"ngram\": \"the ubiquity\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3667}, {\"ngram\": \"sports metaphors\", \"from\": 3671, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"how much the mentality\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3746}, {\"ngram\": \"all costs\", \"from\": 3780, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"our society's obsession\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3830}, {\"ngram\": \"achievement\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end, forcing ourselves to finish things just to finish them becomes absurd-an invitation to reevaluate for those toiling on seemingly endless projects.\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 4007, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3859}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 3889, \"to\": 3895}, {\"ngram\": \"absurd-an invitation\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3944}, {\"ngram\": \"seemingly endless projects\", \"from\": 3980, \"to\": 4006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If Sisyphus were an athlete, he would have been the best,\\\" Chen writes wryly, \\\"the universe's one standout stone-roller.\", \"from\": 4008, \"to\": 4129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4012, \"end\": 4020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisyphus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.243550697240228e-14, \"text\": \"Sisyphus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisyphus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sisyphus\"}, {\"begin\": 4068, \"end\": 4072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\", \"score\": 0.8365024348998971, \"rank\": 0.14264776926386544, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen-style_taijiquan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4036}, {\"ngram\": \"the universe's one standout stone-roller\", \"from\": 4088, \"to\": 4128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"- Chelsea Leu From our list: Eight books to read if you are in a creative slump \\ud83d\\udcdaSomeone Like Us, by Dinaw Mengestu \\ud83d\\udcdaThe Horse: A Galloping History of Humanity,by Timothy C. Winegard \\ud83d\\udcdaThe Missing Thread: A Women's History of the Ancient World,by Daisy Dunn When Good Pain Turns Into Bad Pain By Amanda Parrish Morgan During the years I was dreaming of martyrdom, the future national champion Lauren Fleshman was a high-school athlete as well, on her way to becoming one of the most accomplished American distance runners in history.\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4224, \"end\": 4231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Like_Us\", \"score\": 0.9999995078393414, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Like Us\", \"types\": [\"Q482994\", \"Q386724\", \"Q218818